LAFIA – Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu, National Leader and one of the presidential aspirants on the platform of the All Progressives Congress (APC) on Friday, met with the Nasarawa State delegates and appealed to them to vote for him during the forthcoming party primaries election which was scheduled to hold soon. Tinubu, who appealed to delegates to vote for him during his visit in Lafia, said if elected as a president his government would focus on unity, progress and development of Nigeria irrespective of tribal, religious and geopolitical locations. “I want to appealed to you to support my presidential ambition by voting for me to clinch the party’s ticket at the forthcoming primary election. -Advertisement- He said that if elected as a president in 2023, his government would address challenges facing education, and agriculture and tackle prevalent insecurity challenges in the country. Tinubu insisted that he has track records, experience, training and the vision of changing the nation from its current poverty status to prosperity. He said,” Together will stand to defeat terrorists, banditry insecurity and poverty “I am focused, I know the way to end poverty, I know the road to get our children to be educated and fed well, I know the way to stop the strike in the University and upgrade salaries and all of that arguments, I know the way that we most maintain our electric transmission line,I know the fact that there cannot be rapid development rather to pay attention to electricity. On his remarked Abdullahi Sule, the governor of Nasarawa State said Nigerian are yearning for a good candidate who understand what Nigeria needs in order to reposition the country. POLL He added that with Tinubu he is confident that it will be achieved.